Description: I am selling my '58 Fender American Vintage Telecaster. It's a great guitar that I've had for a few years but played very little because a few years ago I started concentrating on playing acoustic guitar. This guitar has the classic styling and sound of the early telecasters few of us can afford now. Now this guitar and the other American Vintage series guitars have been phased out so here's a chance to purchase a great guitar. I have carefully looked the guitar over and my in hand description would be excellent condition with no notable flaws. I just haven't played it enough to show any wear. I am including all the hand tags and case candy that came with the guitar. The strap shown came with the guitar and is included. GUITAR WEIGHS IN AT 7LBS 5OZ. Shipping will be by UPS with insurance and paid by me. I will take it to a store and have it professionally packaged for shipping. Shipping to the lower 48 States only. Payment by PayPal only. Payment expected within 24 hours of auctions end. I will allow a return if not satisfied within 48 hours of receiving guitar. Buyer pays return shipping and must be in same condition as shipped. If you're looking at this auction you probably already know all about this model but it's got specially voiced pickups, thin lacquer finish, tweed case and lot's more. This is info from Fender's web page: Vintage 1958 Telecaster Style For the guitarist who craves pure vintage Fender style, the American Vintage series presents original-era model year guitars built with meticulous attention to accurate detail that bring Fender history and heritage to authentic and exciting new life.Original-era rock 'n' roll was in full swing in 1958, and the Telecaster was right there with it, already a must-have instrument for working guitarists nationwide. Built using original tooling and based on early 1958 models we tracked down, the U.S.-made American Vintage '58 Telecaster is a must-have model for the guitarist who appreciates its place in music history, a transitional year when the Tele took on subtly stylish new design touches, including a "D"-shaped neck profile and staggered bridge pickup pole pieces. Features Ash bodyEarly-1958 neck with "D"-shaped profileSpecially voiced pickups, including staggered bridge-pickup pole magnetsSingle-ply white pickguard"Top hat" switch tip and flat-top knurled chrome control knobsString-through-body bridge with three solid-steel "barrel" saddles
Title: Fender American Vintage '58 Telecaster (Aged White Blonde) Excellent Condition
ConditionDescription: Excellent condition. Used very little. Plastic still on pick guard and all hang tags and original paperwork included.
